"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773878","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-28","<p>Electronic communications are passed across the internet via internet service providers and the routing of an email between an Hon Member and a Government department is dependent on which system and service an email is sent. Ministers’ Private Offices and correspondence teams routinely handle and respond to emails on behalf of their Ministers.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-28T15:56:28.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773878/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773878/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-19","Members: Email","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether electronic communications from hon. Members to Ministers are passed through any third parties before they reach their recipient.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","108821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773879","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-23","<p>Recovery funding is not covered by the Civil Contingencies Act 2004. Following a terrorist attack, as with any emergency, the relevant department or departments responsible for the sectors affected may consider whether to provide recovery funding. I also refer the Hon Member to the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport’s answer to PQ 106697.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-23T14:32:59.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773879/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773879/answer","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773879/answer/previousversion/17141","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-19","Terrorism: Cultural Heritage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether recovery funding, as laid out in the Civil Contingencies Act 2004, is available to public cultural institutions that incur security costs due to terrorist attacks.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","108849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773880","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-29","<p>The new charity is charged with maintaining all of the assets for which the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport has ultimate responsibility. This is determined in the contract with the new charity, which includes five key performance indicators related to this role. This function is reinforced in the objectives of the new charity, one of which is to &quot;protect, conserve maintain and care for the Royal Parks, including their natural and designed landscapes and built environment, to a high standard consistent with their historic, horticultural, environmental and architectural importance.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-29T11:45:12.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773880/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773880/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-19","Royal Parks: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what safeguards in relation to the maintenance of assets were imposed on the Royal Parks when it altered its status to become a charity in 2016.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","108827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773881","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-01","<p>The Government recognises the value of surrogacy as one of a number of options in helping people who can’t have children create a family.</p><p> </p><p>Drafting work on the remedial order is ongoing. We currently estimate it will be laid in the autumn session of Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health supports the proposal by the Law Commission of England and Wales to include a project about surrogacy in its work programme for 2017-20</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-12-01T14:29:10.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773881/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773881/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-19","Surrogate Motherhood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the Government's policy is on the reform of surrogacy law being undertaken by the Law Commission in its 13th Programme of Law Reform.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","108828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773883","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-24","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","108826 ; 108851","2017-10-24T15:59:10.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773883/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773883/answer","108820_ 108826_ 108851.pdf","108820_ 108826_ 108851.pdf","UKSA response","UKSA response","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773883/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-19","Census: Arabs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, for what reason the Office of National Statistics included an ethnic group category for Arabs in the 2011 census.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Gill","108820"
