"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773891","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>As referenced in the answer to question 107910, between January 2016 and 31 March 2017, HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) instructed 42 employers to self-correct identified arrears of over £1.9m to social care workers.</p><p> </p><p>Where employers self-correct arrears owed, HMRC carries out checks to ensure the money is repaid to the workers. HMRC does not recover the arrears.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-24T09:19:37.31Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773891/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773891/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 19 October 2017 to Question 107910, on social services: minimum wage, how much was paid to social care workers through self-correction; and how much was recovered by HM Revenue and Customs between January 2016 and 31 March 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","108857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773893","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Government published a White Paper on the UK’s future customs, VAT and excise plans on 9 October. This sets out the Government’s aim of ensuring that the movement of goods as small parcels, via Royal Mail and fast parcel operators, continues to operate effectively. It can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/customs-bill-legislating-for-the-uks-future-customs-vat-and-excise-regimes</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs is working closely with stakeholders to ensure the movement of goods as small parcels continues to operate effectively after the UK leaves the EU.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-24T09:22:31.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773893/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773893/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","UK Trade with EU: Parcels","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to ensure that the movement of goods as small parcels continues to operate effectively after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","108852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773894","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>During the last Parliament the Government announced over 35 measures and invested a further £800 million in HM Revenue and Customs to tackle tax avoidance and evasion. These measures include the Promoters of Tax Avoidance Schemes regime, introduced in Finance Act 2014, which aims to tackle the behaviour of certain promoters who meet various threshold conditions.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is going further in this Finance Bill with a new Enablers’ penalty which tackles the wider supply chain of those involved in developing and implementing tax avoidance schemes.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-26T11:17:06.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773894/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773894/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Stagecoach Group: KPMG","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the tax tribunal's decision in the case of Stagecoach PLC and Stagecoach Group Holdings Limited v The Commissioners for HM Revenue and Customs, what assessment he has made of the role of KPMG in selling the scheme which the tribunal found to be unlawful.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","108816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773895","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-26T11:15:49.333Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773895/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773895/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","British Home Stores: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in the Government of Jersey on the closing of BHS.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","108773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773896","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>The process of repatriation of the old £1 coins is still ongoing. Coins are being returned to banks by individuals and businesses every day. We encourage those that still have round £1 coins to now bank or donate them to charity.</p><p> </p><p>In all recoinages, a proportion of coin is not returned. We expect that the proportion of round £1 coins removed from circulation to be in line with previous withdrawals of high denomination coins, such as the recoinage of the 50p, which took place between 1997 and 1998.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-10-27T12:01:28.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773896/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773896/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Coinage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the reasons are for there being between 400 and 450 million old, round pound coins still in circulation.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","108795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773898","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-26","<p>I refer the Honourable Member for Luton North to my response to question 105360 on 12 October 2017.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-26T15:00:50.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773898/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773898/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Mossack Fonseca: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress his Department has made in its inquiry into the Panama Papers.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","108775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773899","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>Government has undertaken a significant amount of work to assess the economic impacts of leaving the EU. This is part of our continued programme of rigorous and extensive analytical work on a range of scenarios on a sector by sector basis.</p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister has ‎made clear however that the UK aims to agree an ambitious and comprehensive economic partnership with the EU that is of far greater scope and ambition than any existing free trade agreement.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-27T11:45:09.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773899/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773899/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department's paper, The long-term economic impact of EU membership and the alternatives, published on 18 April 2016, still represents his Department's best assessment of the long-term economic impact of some of the potential trading models available to the UK after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","108741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773900","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>HM Treasury has not made its own estimate of the total costs associated with the collapse of Monarch airline.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-24T10:46:54.923Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773900/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773900/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Monarch Airlines: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of the collapse of Monarch Airlines.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","108714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773901","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>The government is committed to making the welfare system fair for those who pay for it as well as those who benefit from it. This means ensuring that it is appropriately targeted to those that most need support.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-24T11:28:57.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773901/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773901/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to reduce couple penalties for people on universal credit or in receipt of tax credits.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","108671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773903","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>Marriage Allowance was introduced in April 2015, to recognise the importance of marriage in the tax system, and support those on low incomes by helping them keep more of the money they earn.</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) ran a number of advertising campaigns to raise awareness of the savings Marriage Allowance can bring to eligible couples. The first campaign ran between October 2015 to March 2016, and the second between November 2016 to March 2017. A variety of channels were used including press, radio adverts, and digital advertising.</p><p> </p><p>2.4 million couples have successfully claimed Marriage Allowance. In 2017-18, eligible couples can receive a tax reduction of £232, or £662 if they make a backdated claim to 2015-16. Couples who have yet to claim will not lose out as they have until 5 April 2020 to backdate it.</p><p> </p><p>Marriage Allowance can be claimed through the personal tax account, on the GOV.UK website, or by telephone to HMRC.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-24T09:29:54.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773903/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773903/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Married People: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to increase the take-up of the marriage allowance.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","108677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773904","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>Open Banking standards which enable third party interactions with current accounts will be implemented from early 2018.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-24T09:45:40.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773904/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773904/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Bank Services: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the timetable is for the implementation of the Open Banking Standard.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","108679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773905","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>The government keeps all taxes under review at fiscal events, and we will consider this issue carefully as part of the Autumn Budget process.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-10-27T12:02:41.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773905/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773905/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will freeze beer duty in Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","108699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773906","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>The European Investment Bank (EIB), and its offshoot, the European Investment Fund (EIF), have lent significant amounts to UK infrastructure and growth businesses.</p><p> </p><p>It may prove to be in the mutual interest of the UK and the EU to maintain an ongoing relationship between the EIB and UK after the UK has left the EU. The government is looking to explore these options with the EU as part of the negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>Whatever the outcome of the negotiations, it is important that UK businesses have access to the finance they need. As the Chancellor set out in his 2017 Mansion House speech, the government will be prepared in case the UK does not maintain a relationship with the Bank.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-27T11:43:36.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773906/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773906/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","European Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of not being able to access European Investment Bank funds on infrastructure investment after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","108701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773907","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Government has not made an assessment of the merits of protecting customers who wish to use payment initiation services. These consumers are already protected by the Consumer Rights Act 2015, which sets out consumers' rights regarding the arrival and condition of goods and services, and apply regardless of the method of payment used.</p><p>There are separate existing protections that apply to consumers who order a product online but don't recieve it or are dissatisfied in the Consumer Contracts (Information, Cancellation and Additional Charges) Regulations 2013.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-24T10:02:10.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773907/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773907/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Electronic Commerce","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment the Government has made of the potential merits of protecting customers who wish to use payment initiation services under the revised Payment Services Directive in the event that a product they order online does not arrive or meet their expectations.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","108662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773909","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not collect information on whether an individual is attending a college or university as it does not affect the amount of tax due. It is therefore not possible to provide the estimates requested.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","108667","2017-10-24T09:26:53.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773909/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773909/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Students: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the total tax revenue collected from students at colleges and universities in the UK who are working full or part-time during their studies during the (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2015-16 tax year.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","108666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773910","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not collect information on whether an individual is attending a college or university as it does not affect the amount of tax due. It is therefore not possible to provide the estimates requested.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","108666","2017-10-24T09:26:53.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773910/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773910/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Students: Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number and proportion of students at college and university who are liable for income taxation in the UK.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","108667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773911","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>The information for Glasgow East is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC published Child Benefit, Child Tax Credit (CTC) and Working Tax Credit (WTC) take up rates 2014 to 2015 on 14<sup>th</sup> December 2016. This publication is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-benefit-child-tax-credit-ctc-and-working-tax-credit-wtc-take-up-rates-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-benefit-child-tax-credit-ctc-and-working-tax-credit-wtc-take-up-rates-2014-to-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>Table 9 (page 21) provides information on the CTC take up by region, but not parliamentary constituency. This table includes estimates of the number of entitled non-recipients, and are given as central estimates with upper and lower bounds. There is no equivalent table for WTC.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","108656","2017-10-27T11:52:26.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773911/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773911/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Working Tax Credit: Glasgow East","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of people in Glasgow East constituency who are eligible for but do not claim working tax credit payments.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773912","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>The information for Glasgow East is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC published Child Benefit, Child Tax Credit (CTC) and Working Tax Credit (WTC) take up rates 2014 to 2015 on 14<sup>th</sup> December 2016. This publication is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-benefit-child-tax-credit-ctc-and-working-tax-credit-wtc-take-up-rates-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-benefit-child-tax-credit-ctc-and-working-tax-credit-wtc-take-up-rates-2014-to-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>Table 9 (page 21) provides information on the CTC take up by region, but not parliamentary constituency. This table includes estimates of the number of entitled non-recipients, and are given as central estimates with upper and lower bounds. There is no equivalent table for WTC.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","108655","2017-10-27T11:52:26.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773912/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773912/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Child Tax Credit: Glasgow East","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of people in Glasgow East constituency who are eligible for but do not claim child tax credit payments.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773914","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-27","<p>HM Treasury’s Chief Scientific Adviser works closely with the Government Office for Science and its wider network of scientific advisers. In addition, the Second Permanent Secretary is a member of the Prime Minister’s Council for Science and Technology. The department also engages regularly with academics, Research Councils and the National Academies to ensure that policy is informed by independent and expert scientific advice.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-27T11:59:42.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773914/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773914/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-19","Treasury: Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that its activities are informed by proactive and independent scientific advice; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","108644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773915","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>Information on the number of transactions on new build houses where the property was sold as leaseholds is available through Land Registry Price Paid data. This data is available from 1995 onwards.</p><p>This information can be accessed here: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/dataset/land-registry-monthly-price-paid-data" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/dataset/land-registry-monthly-price-paid-data</a></p><p>The Department for Communities and Local Government has recently concluded a public consultation, <em>Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market</em>, which sought views on a range of proposed measures to help tackle abuse of the leasehold system including the sale of new build leasehold houses. The responses are being analysed and Government will publish an official response in due course<strong>. </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T17:17:52.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773915/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773915/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773915/answer/previousversion/17314","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Housing: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information his Department holds on the number of new houses sold as leasehold properties in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","108663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773917","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>We are in active discussion with city region mayors to understand the areas where they would like to undertake further work with Government. We are also engaging with other areas to understand where there is a strong case for devolution.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-10-24T16:50:35.643Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773917/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773917/answer","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773917/answer/previousversion/17317","Biography information for Jake Berry","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Local Government: Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which areas the Government is holding active discussions with on further devolution in England.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","108730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773918","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>Local authorities' expenditure on services, including on Adult Social Care for previous years, can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing</a><br> <br> Councils have also been able to add a precept for adult social care onto their council tax, which most of them have done. <br> <br> Local authority expenditure is funded through a range of income sources including government grants, council tax, business rates and fees and charges. Many government grants are not ring-fenced, leaving local authorities to determine how much is spent on different services. <br> <br> However, the Government has provided specific funding to councils for adult social care in recent years, most noticeably through the improved Better Care Fund which was supplemented by the additional £2 billion announced at Spring Budget 2017. Details of individual council allocations of the Spring Budget funding can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-allocations-of-the-additional-funding-for-adult-social-care" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-allocations-of-the-additional-funding-for-adult-social-care</a><br> <br> Details of the original improved Better Care Fund allocations along with the potential revenue from the precept (as announced at SR15) can be found with core spending power tables published with the LGFS - <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/final-local-government-finance-settlement-england-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/final-local-government-finance-settlement-england-2017-to-2018</a>.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-24T14:00:56.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773918/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773918/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Social Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much funding his Department has allocated to adult social care in (a) Kirklees, (b) West Yorkshire and (c) England in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","108764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773919","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-27","<p>On 22 October my Department launched a Call for Evidence on the home buying and selling process. We have asked how we should best tackle gazumping, and will develop plans in the light of this feedback.</p><p /> <p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-27T13:17:10.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773919/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773919/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Gazumping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he plans to take steps to mitigate the adverse effects of the practice of gazumping in the housing market.","false","Biography information for Neil Parish","Tiverton and Honiton","Neil Parish","108748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773920","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>DCLG publishes regular statistics on rough sleeping, statutory homelessness and homelessness prevention and relief in England. These are published at a local authority level.</p><p>The latest statistics can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics</a>.</p><p>The Government remains committed to reducing homelessness and rough sleeping. No one should ever have to sleep rough. That is why we are aiming to halve rough sleeping by 2022 and eliminate it altogether by 2027. To achieve this, we will set up a new homelessness reduction taskforce that will focus on prevention and affordable housing, and we will pilot a Housing First approach to tackle entrenched rough sleeping.</p><p>We are also implementing in April 2018 the most ambitious legislative reform in decades, the Homelessness Reduction Act, which will ensure that more people get the help they need earlier to prevent them from becoming homeless in the first place.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","108769","2017-10-24T14:03:00.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773920/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773920/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of trends in the level of homelessness in (a) Liverpool, (b) Liverpool City Region, (c) the North West and (d) England; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","108768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773922","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>DCLG publishes regular statistics on rough sleeping, statutory homelessness and homelessness prevention and relief in England. These are published at a local authority level.</p><p>The latest statistics can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics</a>.</p><p>The Government remains committed to reducing homelessness and rough sleeping. No one should ever have to sleep rough. That is why we are aiming to halve rough sleeping by 2022 and eliminate it altogether by 2027. To achieve this, we will set up a new homelessness reduction taskforce that will focus on prevention and affordable housing, and we will pilot a Housing First approach to tackle entrenched rough sleeping.</p><p>We are also implementing in April 2018 the most ambitious legislative reform in decades, the Homelessness Reduction Act, which will ensure that more people get the help they need earlier to prevent them from becoming homeless in the first place.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","108768","2017-10-24T14:03:00.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773922/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773922/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information his Department holds on the number of people who were homeless in (a) Liverpool Walton constituency, (b) Liverpool, (c) Liverpool City Region, (d) the North West and (e) England in each year from 2005 to date.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","108769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773923","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>Developing a workable and sustainable funding model for supported housing is a priority for the Government. We will set out next steps shortly.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-24T14:25:55.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773923/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773923/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Supported Housing: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish his new policy on funding for supported housing.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","108771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773924","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Department does not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p><p>At a Westminster Hall Debate on 5 July I announced the formation of a working group to consider any regulatory issues in the taxi and private hire vehicle sector and potential remedies. The group has been formed with a cross-section of interested parties, including representatives of licensing authorities, the trade, and drivers, among others. The group had its first meeting in September, and I have asked that it reports to me by early 2018.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-10-24T15:00:40.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773924/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773924/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-19","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many private hire vehicles operate in a different local authority area from their area of registration in (a) the North West and (b) England and Wales; and what his policy is on such cross-border activity.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","108802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773925","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Building Safety Programme has identified council and housing association owned residential buildings over 18 metres with Aluminium Composite Material cladding. The latest figures can be found on the Building Safety Programme webpage:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/building-safety-programme" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/building-safety-programme</a>.</p><p>We are using the 18 metre threshold because Building Regulations guidance on fire safety is more stringent for buildings above that height, reflecting the additional complexities of fire fighting and protecting residents from fire in taller buildings.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-24T15:16:42.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773925/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773925/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773925/answer/previousversion/17316","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","High Rise Flats","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of residential buildings over 30 metres high which are owned or managed by a council or housing association.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773927","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-24","<p>Following the General Election, HM Treasury and Cabinet Office Ministers have agreed that Single Departmental Plans (SDPs) will continue to provide the framework for medium-term business planning and performance management. The Government intends to update SDPs later this year.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-24T14:02:05.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773927/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773927/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-19","Department for Communities and Local Government: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether any policy of administrative aims and objectives set out in his Department's single departmental plan for 2015 to 2020 are no longer the aims or objectives of his Department.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","108861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773928","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-26","<p>Yes, as indicated in the consultation on the broadband Universal Service Obligation, a summary of responses will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-26T11:35:20.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773928/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773928/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-19","Broadband: Universal Service Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department plans to provide a response to the consultation on the Broadband Universal Service Obligation that closed on 9 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","108810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773929","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-26","<p>The 5G briefing event in Glasgow is one of three events taking place across the UK to support the launch of the first competition for the Government’s 5G Testbeds &amp; Trials Programme. These events are open to potential bidders, including industry, academic institutions and local areas, and will help to prepare them to submit a proposal. We have advertised these events widely, emailing to over 9000 organisations across the whole of the UK, including Scottish Enterprise. Additional details are on the Innovate UK website, who are running the competition on behalf of DCMS.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-26T11:33:57.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773929/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773929/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-19","5G","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what persons and organisations her Department plans to invite to the Glasgow briefing event on 1 November 2017 which is part of the 5G Testbeds and Trials Programme: Phase 1 funding competition.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773930","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-26","<p>Ministers and officials from the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport meet regularly with their counterparts in the Department for Work and Pensions to discuss a range of issues including tackling digital exclusion.</p><p> </p><p>The Digital Skills and Inclusion chapter of the Digital Strategy, published in March of this year, describes some of the many ways in which we are working across government and with industry and the charity sector to address the digital divide.</p><p> </p><p>Responsibility for digital inclusion in Scotland is devolved, but the UK Government also funds Good Things Foundation to deliver the Future Digital Inclusion Programme. Good Things Foundation oversees the network of more than 5,000 UK Online Centres, including in Glasgow East.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-26T11:32:07.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773930/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773930/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-19","Digital Technology: Glasgow East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 30 June 2017 to Question 90, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions on the potential effect of jobcentre closures in Glasgow East constituency on levels of digital exclusion.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773932","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-24","<p>Freelancers form a vital part of the UK workforce, particularly for the creative industries. The Secretary of State and her ministers have regular discussions on a number of issues that impact the creative industries, including working practices. Self-employed people have greater flexibility over their working hours, including when they take time off work.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-24T16:12:01.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773932/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773932/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-19","Performing Arts: Parental Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the potential benefits to the creative industries of extending shared parental leave to freelance workers.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","108694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773933","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-26","<p>Since the introduction of the Trident Strategic Weapon System in 1994, no US nuclear warhead has been transferred to a Royal Navy submarine. Records prior to 1994 are not held centrally and the information could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-26T13:39:45.55Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773933/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773933/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-19","USA: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list the occasions on which US nuclear warheads have been transferred to British submarines.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","108774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773934","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-27","<p>The Secretary of State for Defence has not had any discussions with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on lifting the public sector pay cap for members of the Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-27T13:17:40.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773934/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773934/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-19","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on lifting the public sector pay cap for members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","108710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773936","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-26","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 made provision to augment the Queen Elizabeth Class Aircraft Carriers and maximise their ability to support amphibious operations. Prior to the carriers being brought into service, other Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary ships will continue to provide support to amphibious operations.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-26T13:40:11.297Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773936/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773936/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-19","Amphibious Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to enhance the Royal Navy's amphibious forces as set out in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","108804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773937","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-24","<p>Information is only readily available for the 2016 and 2017 seasons.</p><p>The Red Arrows conducted 267 displays over the 2016 to 2017 season, with only 13 of these being flown with fewer than the standard nine aircraft.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-24T16:56:49.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773937/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773937/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-19","Red Arrows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the oral contribution of the Leader of the House of 19 October 2017, Official Report, column 1023, how many Red Arrows flew in each display since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","108839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773938","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-25","<p>The final bids in respect of the Defence Fire and Rescue Project were received on 19 September 2017. These bids are now being assessed and, subject to receiving the necessary approvals, the contract is expected to be awarded in 2018.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-10-25T13:37:29.743Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773938/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773938/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-19","Defence Fire Risk Management Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timetable is for awarding the Defence Fire Risk Management Organisation contract; and when the successful bidder of that contract will commence mobilisation.","false","Biography information for Sir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","The Cotswolds","Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","108815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773939","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Ministry of Defence publishes annual statistics on vessels, land equipment and aircraft of the Armed Forces, as well as military formations. The information requested can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-armed-forces-equipment-and-formations-2017</p><p> </p><p>We do not routinely comment on specific levels of readiness for individual capabilities as to do so would compromise operational security, or would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","108789 ; 108790","2017-10-24T15:15:20.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773939/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773939/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-19","Warrior Armoured Vehicle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Warrior Infantry Fighting Vehicles the British Army has in (a) active service, (b) immediate reserve and (c) storage.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","108788"
