"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773008","Home Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>There is no specific guidance on the costs of gifts presented to new citizens at citizenship ceremonies. The cost of the gift is covered within the £80 ceremony fee.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-11-01T13:40:47.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773008/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773008/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-18","British Nationality: Ceremonies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what guidance is given to local councils on the costs of gifts presented to new British citizens at citizenship ceremonies.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL2209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773009","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-30","<p>In 2013 the Commission launched infraction proceedings against six member states. These were Belgium, Cyprus, Finland, France, Greece and Slovenia.</p><p> </p><p>A Report from the European Commission to the European Parliament and to the Council in September 2016 states that the Commission’s actions to encourage all Member States to enforce the 2013 partial ban on the keeping of sows in sow stalls proved effective.</p><p> </p><p>There are no EU marketing rules to prevent imports of pig meat from non-compliant production systems.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2017-10-30T12:18:14.55Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773009/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773009/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/773009/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-18","Pigs: Animal Welfare","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government (1) what measures they have taken in relation to any EU member states that are not in compliance with the sow stall ban contained in EU Directive 2008/120/EC; (2) which states have been subject to such measures; and (3) whether pork imports into the UK from non-compliant countries continue to be allowed.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2210"
